<TITLE> Fire guts over 100 shanties in Arambagh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 6 (bdnews24.com)Over 100 shanties were gutted in a fire at the Arambagh slum in Mirpur on Tuesday. The firefighters reported no causalities. The fire began at around 4pm and was doused within an hour, deputy director of Dhaka Zone fire service Abdur Rashid told bdnews24.com. The reason behind could not be identified immediately, but he suspected it might have been from a cooking stove. Rashid said the fire spread fast through the dry bamboo huts. There were, however, no estimations on the amount of damages. bdnews24.c
